cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for pattern recognition tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves transfer learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of filter-trees to improve efficiency in learning CNNs is a novel approach, which could also fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes simulations to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which could be considered a multimedia topic (cs.MM).
